</E>@}</EBODY><SOLN/>@{<WR>
Shall show that <M>K</M>  is closed, ie, <M>K^c</M>  is open, ie

<TGT>\forall x\in K^c~~\exists U\in \tau~~x\in U\seq K^c.</TGT>
<FLL>x</FLL>Take any <M>x\in K^c.</M>  

Then <M>\forall y\in K~~x\neq y.</M>

So, by the <M>T_2</M>  property, 
<D>\exists A_y, B_y\in \tau~~A_y\cap B_y=\phi,~~x\in A_y\mbox{ and } y\in B_y.</D>
Then <M>\{B_y~:~y\in K\}</M>  is an open cover for <M>K.</M>

Since <M>K</M>  is compact, we can extract a finite subcover <M>\{B_{y_1},...,B_{y_n}\}.</M>  

<EXS>U</EXS> Choose <M>U = \cap_{i=1}^n A_{y_i}\in\tau.</M>

<CHK/>Then <M>U\seq (*(\cup B_{y_i})*)^c \seq K^c.</M>
</WR>@}</EXM>




